      "node_id": "chunk:smodcast_pictures_0",
      "passage_index": 9,
      "title": "SModcast Pictures",
      "score": 0.09783733296142158,
      "text": "SModcast Pictures\nSModcast Pictures is an American film distribution company and a film and television production company founded by Kevin Smith in 2011. Kevin Smith announced at the 2011 Sundance Film Festival that he would release his latest movie \"Red State\" himself under his own distribution company \"SModcast Pictures\" by touring the film instead of having a traditional release.",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.05041503564685969,
        "graph": 0.05638324232616515,
        "fact": 0.3546272710519947
      }
    },
    {
      "node_id": "chunk:amblin_entertainment_0",
      "passage_index": 18,
      "title": "Amblin Entertainment",
      "score": 0.09485035829195368,
      "text": "Amblin Entertainment\nAmblin Entertainment is an American film production company founded by director and producer Steven Spielberg, and film producers Kathleen Kennedy and Frank Marshall in 1981. The company's headquarters are located on the backlot of Universal Studios in Universal City, California. The company distributes all of the films from Amblin Partners under the Amblin Entertainment name.",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.05035041422871315,
        "graph": 0.05687076767680416,
        "fact": 0.333976001087468
      }
    },
    {
      "node_id": "chunk:mike_medavoy_0",
      "passage_index": 6,
      "title": "Mike Medavoy",
      "score": 0.09026202253230095,
      "text": "Mike Medavoy\nMorris Mike Medavoy (born January 21, 1941) is an American film producer and executive, co-founder of Orion Pictures (1978), former chairman of TriStar Pictures, former head of production for United Artists (1974–1978) and current chairman and CEO of Phoenix Pictures.",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.050116674444791766,
        "graph": 0.053294474695282965,
        "fact": 0.31139672786053724
      }
    },
    {
      "node_id": "chunk:uhf_film_0",
      "passage_index": 10,
      "title": "UHF (film)",
      "score": 0.04284547473442599,
      "text": "UHF (film)\nYankovic and Levey wrote the film after Yankovic's second studio album, looking to apply the musician's parody and comedy to film, and chose the approach of George being a straight man with a vivid imagination to support the inclusion of parodies within the film. They struggled with finding a film production company for financing the film, but were eventually able to get Orion Pictures' support after stating they could keep the film costs under $5 million. Principal filming took place around Tulsa, Oklahoma, with many of the extras for the film from the Tulsa and Dallas, Texas areas.",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.05066440745515194,
        "graph": 0.0499335021136414,
        "fact": 0.0
      }
    },
    {
      "node_id": "chunk:marketwired_0",
      "passage_index": 15,
      "title": "Marketwired",
      "score": 0.0422569015870143,
      "text": "Marketwired\nMarketwired is a press release distribution service headquartered in Toronto, Ontario, Canada. Marketwired was founded in 1993 and incorporated in the U.S. in 1999. The company distributes press releases via traditional methods (Associated Press, Bloomberg, etc.) as well as new media methods and other services.",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.05011366627215358,
        "graph": 0.04898128379109943,
        "fact": 0.0
      }
    },
    {
      "node_id": "chunk:videodrome_0",
      "passage_index": 4,
      "title": "Videodrome",
      "score": 0.04223317016606773,
      "text": "Videodrome\nVideodrome is a 1983 Canadian science fiction body horror film written and directed by David Cronenberg and starring James Woods, Sonja Smits, and Deborah Harry. Set in Toronto during the early 1980s, it follows the CEO of a small UHF television station who stumbles upon a broadcast signal featuring extreme violence and torture. The layers of deception and mind-control conspiracy unfold as he uncovers the signal's source, and loses touch with reality in a series of increasingly bizarre and violent organic hallucinations.",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.05006958182518077,
        "graph": 0.04898300054072768,
        "fact": 0.0
      }
    },
