      "title": "Equity Music Group",
      "score": 0.04221393924454908,
      "text": "Equity Music Group\nEquity Music Group was an American country music record label founded in 2003 by singer Clint Black. The label was distributed by Koch Entertainment (now E1 Entertainment).",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.05004398762992497,
        "graph": 0.04896582016030116,
        "fact": 0.0
      }
    },
    {
      "node_id": "chunk:three_gut_records_0",
      "passage_index": 8,
      "title": "Three Gut Records",
      "score": 0.04220835759642972,
      "text": "Three Gut Records\nThree Gut Records was a Guelph, Ontario, Canada based independent record label. It was founded in 1999 by Lisa Moran and Tyler Clarke Burke as a vehicle for releasing albums by their friends; it became an influential player in Canadian music with the breakout success of the Constantines' self-titled 2001 release on the label. Three Gut releases were distributed by Outside Music.",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.0500323359404633,
        "graph": 0.04896857609724967,
        "fact": 0.0
      }
    },
    {
      "node_id": "chunk:desoto_records_0",
      "passage_index": 3,
      "title": "DeSoto Records",
      "score": 0.042205674085878706,
      "text": "DeSoto Records\nDeSoto Records is an American record label based in Washington, D.C. Founded in 1989, it is run by Bill Barbot and Kim Coletta, both formerly of the band Jawbox. It was first founded by members of the band Edsel to release their first single, \"My Manacles\". Jawbox next used the name DeSoto for their first EP. It has released over 40 records, 7\" singles, CDs, and LP vinyl records. It is distributed by Fontana Distribution.",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.05000926759593725,
        "graph": 0.049001923027044064,
        "fact": 0.0
      }
    },
    {
      "node_id": "chunk:sleaszy_rider_records_0",
      "passage_index": 11,
      "title": "Sleaszy Rider Records",
      "score": 0.04219387552532173,
      "text": "Sleaszy Rider Records\nSleaszy Rider Records is an independent record label which was founded in 1999 by Tolis G. Palantzas. The head office of the label is located in Greece. The label is mainly distributed in Europe by Sony Music/EMI. The label also distributes releases in Greece from numerous labels, including Roadrunner Records, SPV, and Pagan Records.",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.04999433915399444,
